-- Russia’s Pork Output Climbed 34% in July Versus Year Earlier
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2013-08-19T12:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-19/russia-s-pork-output-climbed-34-in-july-versus-year-earlier.html
Russia’s production of beef, pork
and poultry increased in July compared with a year earlier, the
Federal State Statistics Service, known as Rosstat, said in an
e-mailed statement.  Pork output gained 34 percent to 104,000 metric tons and
poultry production rose 1.8 percent to 294,000 tons, Rosstat
said today. Production of beef and meat from other cattle rose
1.8 percent to 14,800 tons.  Cattle and poultry production by live weight, which
includes skin, bones and byproducts, rose 9.2 percent to 900,000
tons in July compared with the year earlier, according to
Rosstat.  Russia’s cattle herd fell 1.9 percent from last year to
20.9 million head by the end of July and the number of cows
dropped 1.7 percent to 9 million, according to the statement.
The number of hogs gained 5.2 percent to 20.5 million and the
number of sheep and goats fell 0.3 percent to 27.2 million.  Editor:  To contact the reporter on this story:
